<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="bwmorph" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>bwmorph</refname><refpurpose>Dispatch common binary morphology operations.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = bwmorph(image, operation); out = bwmorph(image, operation, iterations)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 2D image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>operation</term><listitem><para><literal>thin</literal>, <literal>skel</literal>, <literal>fill</literal>, <literal>erode</literal>, <literal>dilate</literal>, <literal>open</literal>, <literal>close</literal>, <literal>tophat</literal>, <literal>bothat</literal>, or <literal>hitmiss</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>iterations</term><listitem><para>Positive iteration count. Default is 1.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>bwmorph</function> provides a single dispatch interface over IPCV morphology primitives. It intentionally supports the documented operation subset rather than silently approximating unsupported MATLAB operators.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[mask = zeros(9, 9) == 1; mask(3:7, 5) = %t; mask(5, 3:7) = %t; skeleton = bwmorph(mask, "thin");]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="bwthin">bwthin</link></member><member><link linkend="imdilate">imdilate</link></member><member><link linkend="imerode">imerode</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
